news.title: Oberoi Realty posts net profit of Rs 403.08 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 934.81 crore in Q1 FY23, a growth of 217 per cent from Rs 294.77 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bombay HC raps government for stalling demolition of illegal buildings
news.para: The court was hearing a PIL filed in 2021 by three persons on the issue of the April 2014 collapse of a building in Lucky Compound in Mumbra that killed some 80 people.

news.title: Rajasthan's UDH minister approves policy to open sealed buildings in Jaipur
news.para: Under this policy, the director of the directorate of local bodies (DLB) has been empowered to open the sealing of illegally constructed buildings in the municipal corporation, municipality and municipal council areas.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Probe team unearths building number fraud in Kunnukuzhy ward
news.para: The issue is snowballing into a major headache for the civic body as two revenue officials were summoned for questioning by the police probe team on Thursday in connection with the fraud in Kesavadasapuram ward.

news.title: SBI hikes lending rates by 10 basis points
news.para: The country's largest lender State Bank of India has decided to increase its marginal cost of lending rate (MCLR) on loans by 10 basis points or 0.10 per cent effective from July 15, 2022.

news.title: Bengaluru: RLDA invites bids for 8.61 acres land at Cantonment Railway Colony
news.para: The reserve price of the land is Rs 236 crore for a lease period of 60 years.  The site is approachable by Miller’s Road and Cantonment Road from the north and Thimmaiah Road from the west.

news.title: ED freezes Rs 95 crore worth bank deposits after raids on Rashmi Group
news.para: The money laundering case stems from a CBI FIR against the Rashmi group of companies. These include Rashmi Cement Ltd and Rashmi Metalik Ltd.

news.title: Zara founder in talks to buy $500-million New York skyscraper
news.para: The planned acquisition follows recent Pontegadea deals in Scotland to buy one of the largest single-office buildings and in Toronto, where it bought the Royal Bank Plaza, a landmark skyscraper, which houses the headquarters of the Royal Bank of Canada, for around $797.92 million.

news.title: Local body cannot levy property tax from company in industrial development area: HC
news.para: The ruling was given by justice Shaji P Chaly after considering a petition (WP-C No. 3603/2016) filed by Holmarc Opto Mechatronics Pvt Ltd, which has an industrial unit at Kalamassery IDA at HMT Industrial Estate.

news.title: After original Chandigarh housing board allottees die, heirs need new licences
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said policy decision was taken about the transfer of small flats under Chandigarh Small Flats Scheme 2006, where both the allottees have expired after allotment.

news.title: Jharkhand: Over 4,000 PMAY-Gramin defaulters in Palamu to face heat
news.para: Most of the defaulters, sources said, have diverted the funds for some other purpose while some have built a portion of their house but now they are no longer interested in completing the construction.

news.title: Gurugram: Developer settles power infrastructure dues, discom to refund Ardee City residents
news.para: However, as DHBVN cannot refund in cash, the power discom has decided to add the amount collected from the residents as ‘development charges’ to their respective electricity account as advance payment so as to adjust the money against future power bills.

news.title: Basic Home Loan to disburse Rs 1,000 crore every month by March 2023
news.para: Basic Home Loan has aggressive expansion plan for 2022-23 and will be present in over 100 cities from about 30 cities currently.

news.title: NBCC to settle with home buyers of NBCC Green View
news.para: "..the company has decided to settle with all the homebuyers/allottees by way of buy-back of their flats/units and to do all such acts, deeds and things, necessary, incidental & ancillary to give effect to the same," NBCC said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Kapil Wadhawan sanctioned loans of over Rs 400 crore without following norms: CBI
news.para: The agency filed the additional charge sheet in the case of cheating against Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and Dewan Housing Finance Limited (DHFL) promoters Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan last month.
